text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus setulosa is the accepted name of a tree species in the Asian sub-genus of 'ring-cupped oaks' and the family Fagaceae.
text.Subspecies and Description:
The Catalogue of Life lists the following:
Q. setulosa laotica
Q. setulosa setulosaThis oak tree grows up to 30 m tall and has been recorded from Laos and Vietnam (especially the Central Highlands), where it may be called sồi duối.
